   Example 5:  '.'      Display info about all pin's I/O configuration and states.

 pin 0  I  hi-z
 pin 1  I  hi-z
 pin 2  O  high
 pin 3  O  low
 pin 4  I  hi-z
*pin 5  I  pullup       // * indicates the selected pin
 pin 6  I  hi-z
 pin 7  I  hi-z
 pin 8  I  hi-z
 pin 9  I  hi-z
 pin 10 I  hi-z
 pin 11 I  hi-z
 pin 12 I  hi-z
 pin 13 I  pullup



